Management
 What is the CEO of LocalShares Investment Trust - Nashville Area ETF's salary, the management and board of directors tenure and is there insider trading?

Management is one of the most important areas of a company. We look at unreasonable CEO compensation, how long the team and board of directors have been around for and insider trading.



CEO








Bill Decker





CEO Bio

Mr. William S. Decker, also known as Bill, serves as the Chief Investment Officer at LocalShares, Inc. Mr. Decker is also the Founder, Managing Member, and Portfolio Manager at Decker Wealth Management, LLC. He is responsible for development and application of investment strategies for clients. Mr. Decker career experience includes more than 11 years at Morgan Stanley, where he served as a Senior Vice President of Investments and more than five years at US Trust/Bank of America, where he served as a Senior Vice President and Private Client Advisor. He focused on wealth management for high net worth individuals and families. Mr. Decker applied the mix of economics and political science at his first job in the City of Los Angeles. He serves as a Director of LocalShares, Inc. He held one intensive program at the University of Pennsylvania’s Wharton School of Business. Mr. Decker completed his undergraduate studies at Baylor University, earning a Bachelor’s degree with a Public Administration major. He also earned an M.B.A. from Pepperdine University.


